    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. but what happens if the inspection goes bad? like if they find some serious structural issues with the foundation or something... can i get that money back then? or is it stuck in the escrow account regardless?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the inspection reveals serious issues, you usually have contractual rights to address that within the terms of your purchase agreement. You can often use the earnest money as leverage to negotiate repairs, request a price reduction, or, if the issues are too severe, walk away from the deal. If you legally terminate the contract due to the inspection findings, the earnest money is usually returned to you from the escrow account. It isn't stuck there indefinitely if the deal falls through based on agreed-upon contingencies.",
      "source": "target",
