    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow account is managed by a neutral third party, which is often a title company or a specialized escrow company, rather than a standard bank account. This entity's job is to hold the funds securely and follow the written instructions of the purchase agreement meticulously. They act as the official custodian, ensuring that money only moves to the correct party (buyer or seller) once every condition of the sale has been verifiably met. They are essentially the impartial referee for the transaction's finances.",
